overview: The user initiated a request for comprehensive browser testing of the
  Sleep Questionnaire application. The agent began by verifying the dev server
  status and then navigated through the application. It tested the main
  questionnaire flow, including filling out sections and observing conditional
  field rendering. The "Pre-fill & Jump to Report (Dev)" button was utilized to
  quickly test the report generation, and the PDF download functionality was
  successfully verified. Subsequently, the agent attempted to test the admin
  dashboard, confirming that the login page was protected and successfully
  validating the error handling for incorrect passwords. During testing, a
  potential navigation bug was identified where the "Previous" button appeared
  to move forward instead of backward, and a possible React rendering timing
  issue was noted, affecting the accuracy of immediate browser snapshots.
